    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Thin vaults of one or more layers of terracotta tiles laid flat edge to edge and deriving their rigidity from cohesion and curvature rather than from massiveness or compression; can be erected without centering.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
